last_episode_to_air.name: Finale
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Gem Quest that Danny long ignored comes back to haunt him when Bug's beloved pet, Hank Flappington, is stolen for the gem-engine Danny gave Bug to power him.

name: Future-Worm!
overview: The show follows Danny Douglas and his friend Future-Worm as they go on adventures and travel through time.

episodes.name: Long Live Captain Cakerz!
episodes.overview: Danny's attempt to watch his favorite show Steak Starbolt while eating his favorite cereal, Captain Cakerz, is interrupted when the breakfast cereal is out of stock, so he travels back to get them. However, he and Future-Worm figure out who stole the cereal â€” an alien race called Gloopies, which the citizens end up as their slaves, including Danny's parents! But to save them, Danny and Fyootch uses help from their friend Bug and a special guest as well as boxes of Cakerz.

episodes.name: Terrible Tuber Trouble
episodes.overview: Danny uses a future chemistry set he just obtained in order to make an anniversary dinner for his parents upon them cashing in their favor coupon. This experiment ends up creating a mashed potato monster.

episodes.name: Healin' Touch with Dr. D
episodes.overview: Upon Danny getting brain freeze after drinking a slushie, Future-Worm takes him to the year 3,000 where he ends up on a medical TV show called Healin' Touch with Dr. D where the titular doctor is a Tyrannosaurus.

episodes.name: How to Beat a Cold... With Fists!
episodes.overview: Danny has a highly contagious cold and can't go to the latest Steak Starbolt convention. He then accidentally creates a giant cold monster while his dad faces his fear of germs.

episodes.name: Old Man Duck Head
episodes.overview: Danny and Future-Worm laugh at an old man as a duck is on his head. But Future-Worm knows that laughing too hard can never make you laugh again, so he and Danny travel back to see if it's true. This was interrupted as the duck-head man is elected president.

episodes.name: Unsolved Histories
episodes.overview: On "Unsolved Histories," Baxter Frost talks about how Danny and Fyootch change time when they can't afford a burrito on Columbus Day. As the Time Machine Lunch Box knocks out in 1492, the year Christopher Columbus first discovered America, the man closes down stores for the day! But the duo change his name to Christopher Burrito in order to get burritos.

episodes.name: Meetiversary
episodes.overview: Future-Worm forgets to get Danny a gift. When they go to outer space, they discover that scientists have turned into werewolves.

episodes.name: Steak Starbolt
episodes.overview: Steak Starbolt is too busy fighting giant robots and monsters, with his crew thinking he's dead.

episodes.name: The Very Hungry Killah-Pillah
episodes.overview: Bug creates a "truck-o-sarus" and she and the boys must tame it, yet that it metamorphosizes into a truck butterfly.

episodes.name: Bubble Dad
episodes.overview: Danny creates a hermetically-sealed bubble for his dad when they show up at camp.

episodes.name: Porthole to the Lizard
episodes.overview: Danny finds himself in detention and must escape in order to see a Komodo dragon.

episodes.name: Future Danny and the Ghost Pirates of Tau Ceti
episodes.overview: Future Danny finds himself captured by pirate ghosts.

episodes.name: Deunited
episodes.overview: With Danny at his aunt's house, Fyootch spends the day with Bug when doing a cheese explosion. However, Future-Worm is kidnapped by birds.

episodes.name: The Forever Five
episodes.overview: After Megan creates her latest invention, the Forever Five, she, Danny, and Fyootch are teleported to a world where everything is gray and its inhabitants are depressed, by a sad princess who wants to use Megan's invention to make her subjects happy.

episodes.name: Great Debates with the End of Time
episodes.overview: Fyootch and Danny fight to see what animal it is: either a fish or a pig.

episodes.name: The Bleak Shall Inherit the Earth
episodes.overview: Danny wanted to be the biggest fan of rock band Titanium White...until he and Fyootch visit an alternative timeline.

episodes.name: Makin' History
episodes.overview: Danny brings a lobster boy for a school project, and later teaches him how to play football.

episodes.name: Lobster Boy Movie Trailer
episodes.overview: Lobster Boy dreams of becoming part of the school's football team in a fake movie trailer.

episodes.name: Go Help Yourself
episodes.overview: Future-Worm leaves Danny to do one last job for a friend.

episodes.name: Barl
episodes.overview: Future-Worm and Danny go on a road trip with Barl.

episodes.name: Mecha-Muck Wars
episodes.overview: Fyootch leads an army of rebellions.

episodes.name: Revenge of the Anchovy Monster
episodes.overview: The anchovy monster again seeks revenge on Danny and Fyootch.

episodes.name: Food Goggles
episodes.overview: Danny invents "food goggles", which makes everything taste good.

episodes.name: Steak Starbolt Spooktacular
episodes.overview: Steak Starbolt thinks he's stuck inside a TV when doing a public service announcement.

episodes.name: Robo-Carp-Alypse
episodes.overview: Danny's exploding Robo-Carps return as zombies.

episodes.name: The Reemen
episodes.overview: Terrifying creatures invade Danny's house.

episodes.name: Dr. D, Ghost Hunter
episodes.overview: Dr. D becomes a ghost hunter.

episodes.name: Steak Starmom
episodes.overview: When Danny and Fyootch get sucked into the Steak Starbolt virtual reality game, Danny's mom Megan accidentally gets sucked in as well.

episodes.name: Lemonade's Last Stand
episodes.overview: The duo open up a lemonade stand in a future with no lemons.

episodes.name: This Week in Future Science
episodes.overview: The future scientists (who created Future-Worm) also create more abominations of nature.

episodes.name: The Time Travelers Council
episodes.overview: Danny travels back in an attempt to prevent himself from being grounded.

episodes.name: Future Danny and the Scourge of the Plierates
episodes.overview: The Plierates' ritual is interrupted by Future Danny.

episodes.name: Bug's Very Important Job
episodes.overview: Future Danny is paid for a visit to Bug.

episodes.name: Bug vs. the Babysitter
episodes.overview: Bug tries many ways to ditch Zoe, her babysitter.

episodes.name: Doug Race: 3939
episodes.overview: Danny's newest invention ensues chaos when it is tested on his dad.

episodes.name: The Panama Bananama
episodes.overview: The boys visit Danny's aunt Bitsy, when she was young.

episodes.name: Future-Worm and the 54 Days of Snordfest
episodes.overview: Embarrassed by his role in a holiday movie, Fyootch travels to Snordfest to make sure it never happens. The Douglas' leave Doug at the mall where he's adopted into a new family.

episodes.name: Lost in the Mall
episodes.overview: The family accidentally leaves Doug at the mall while Christmas shopping; when they go back for him, they discover a sinister plan afoot in Santa's Village.

episodes.name: Devil on Bug's Shoulder
episodes.overview: Bug uses a coupon to get an adventurous sidekick of her own.

episodes.name: Assassin Parrot
episodes.overview: Danny gets a pet parrot that turns out to be a time-traveling assassin robot.

episodes.name: The Never-Ending End of Time
episodes.overview: Danny and Fyootch's End of Time debate continues.

episodes.name: Egg in the Family
episodes.overview: Ruby and Paco "babysit" an egg for a class project.

episodes.name: The Right to Bear Arms
episodes.overview: Fyootch grows a pair of bear claws to enter a wrestling contest.

episodes.name: This Week in Future Science 2
episodes.overview: Brad and Rad genetically engineer a cool Horseshoe Crab.

episodes.name: Danny Swap: The Musical
episodes.overview: Danny swaps places with Future Danny.

episodes.name: The World According to Larp
episodes.overview: When Danny gives Presto the future-magic-wand, the bad guy becomes more of a bad guy.

episodes.name: Mecha-Muck Wars 2
episodes.overview: Future-Worm learns the price of sacrifice...again.

episodes.name: O Brother, Here Art Thou
episodes.overview: A wedge comes between Danny and Future-Worm.

episodes.name: Life With Barl
episodes.overview: Barl moves into the Douglas' shed.

episodes.name: Fyootch Fails
episodes.overview: Fyootch tries to stop the production of an embarrassing future TV show called Top Ten Future-Worm Fails.

episodes.name: Megan Muck Wars
episodes.overview: Future-Worm attempts to prevent the Mecha-Muck Wars.

episodes.name: Porthole to the Spider Hole
episodes.overview: Bug must learn to overcome her fear of spiders.

episodes.name: Weenie Genie
episodes.overview: Danny and Fyootch order a magical hot dog.

episodes.name: Be Mine Across Time
episodes.overview: Danny and Fyootch's time travel road trip is put on hold when Fyootch begins dating a cave woman named Ooga.

episodes.name: Fyootchy Swap
episodes.overview: Mr. Larzid takes over Fyootch's body in an attempt to get Danny to join the Gem Force Five.

episodes.name: Steak Starbolt Movie Trailer
episodes.overview: A trailer for the Steak Starbolt movie in which Steak must impersonate the President of the United States to stop an assassination plot by his brother.

episodes.name: Manchovy Prison Break
episodes.overview: Future-Worm and Danny reluctantly team up with Manchovy to break him out of prison so that they can protect his gem stash from Future Granny Danny.

episodes.name: Wrong Place, Wrong Time
episodes.overview: Clock Face mistakenly attends a villain's meeting where Future Granny Danny reveals her plan to use the 99 Gems of Mystery and Space on a wish to destroy all timelines except her own.

episodes.name: Future Danny Finale
episodes.overview: After once again escaping from the clutches of the Plierates, Future Danny settles in for some relaxation only to be captured by Future Granny Danny.

episodes.name: Finale
episodes.overview: The Gem Quest that Danny long ignored comes back to haunt him when Bug's beloved pet, Hank Flappington, is stolen for the gem-engine Danny gave Bug to power him.
